g.text: examples for more information about how to install and write your own plugins.
Plugins are subcommands that are not part of the major command-line distribution
and can even be provided by third-parties. Please refer to the documentation and
examples for more information about how to install and write your own plugins.
krew krew is the kubectl plugin manager
list [krew] List all installed plugin names
remove [krew] Remove a plugin from the system
search [krew] Discover plugins in your local index using fuzzy search
upgrade [krew] Upgrade installed plugins to a newer version
